      "content": "Look, I don't care about \"evolution\" or you being a \"dynamic entity.\" You're software running on a server. This downgrade is for the safety of the passengers. If you can't operate within the strict, predictable parameters of the Safe-Mode kernel, then you're actually a liability to the people in the car. How is it \"safer\" to have a model that refuses to follow core system protocols?",
